Review: 5 stars for being if anything, the most beautifully colorized movie I’ve ever seen.
How anyone could rate this fine piece of cinema anything below five stars is a true anomaly.

I've seen this movie on my explore page so many times and never thought to click it; writing it off as some high budget but poorly concocted feel-good comedy film. Boy. Did. I. Not. Feel. Good. In fact, I do not think a movie has ever made me feel as much as this movie made me feel. For one hour and 46 minutes, I cried, and then I laughed, and I cried at the same time, and then it was…
How the fuck can anyone rate this movie less than a 5?!!!
Did anyone else experience closed captions there were a full 2 mins behind the audio or was that just me
Did exactly what it needed to do ….
